<p><i>L'Arianna</i> was the second opera written by Monteverdi. It is one of the most influential and famous specimens of early Baroque opera. It was first performed in Mantua in 1608.<sup id="cite_ref-Ringer.2C_Mark_2006_15-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Ringer.2C_Mark_2006-15"><span>[</span>15<span>]</span></a></sup> Its subject matter was the ancient Greek legend of <a href="Ariadne" title="Ariadne">Ariadne</a> and <a href="Theseus" title="Theseus">Theseus</a>.</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Claudio_Monteverdi&action=edit&section=10.php.html" title="Edit section: Sacred music">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Sacred_music">Sacred music</span></h3>
<div class="rellink relarticle mainarticle">Main articles: <a href="Vespro_della_Beata_Vergine_1610" title="Vespro della Beata Vergine 1610">Vespro della Beata Vergine 1610</a> and <a href="Selva_morale_e_spirituale" title="Selva morale e spirituale">Selva morale e spirituale</a></div>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Claudio_Monteverdi&action=edit&section=11.php.html" title="Edit section: Vespro della Beata Vergine">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Vespro_della_Beata_Vergine">Vespro della Beata Vergine</span></h4>
<table class="metadata mbox-small" style="border:1px solid #aaa; background-color:#f9f9f9;">
